            <div type="note">
                <head type="title">Ruskin's Literary Trustees</head>
                <p> By terms of Ruskin&#x02BC;s will, Alexander Wedderburn, Charles Eliot Norton, and Joan
                    Severn were named as trustees <!--Entry needed here.-->. Norton disagreed with the aim of
                    comprehensiveness in the Library Edition, yet he went on himself to publish his
                    own correspondence with Ruskin, violating Wedderburn&#x02BC;s attempts to control
                    further piecemeal publication of letters. (See Dearden, &#x201C;Library Edition of the Works
                    of John Ruskin,&#x201D; 52-53, 59.)</p>

            </div>
